  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for the Mobilization of Young People, Actors of Social Cohesion and Peace in the Center North and Sahel Regions of Burkina Faso</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project responds to the need to strengthen social cohesion between host communities and displaced populations of the Center North and Sahel regions in Burkina Faso. With the aim to carry out activities to help prevent or reduce existing tensions and to strengthen social cohesion between communities, through this project, IOM focuses on placing the public administration at the center of the process in a logic of national and local ownership. The initiative responds to youth problems by bringing together young people from different communities around joint micro-projects selected by the public administration and implemented by micro-grants delivered to youth. Effective communication around the good practices of such young incubators are intended to create multiplier effects at the local and national levels to build and consolidate peace and social cohesion between communities. The project also includes awareness raising and training activities on COVID-19 and other sensitization activities to prepare the population to prevent these risks and avoid potential reject from host communities that could exacerbate vulnerabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
